div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division.
In the Matter of the Application of Antonio Bisegna, alias Disegna, for a Writ of Habeas Corpus. } No.2679

The above entitled matter having come regularly on for hearing on the 20th day of Feburary, 1914, on the Petition for a Writ of Habeas Corpus, the Writ of Habeas Corpus, and respondent's return thereto, and the Court having heard the arguemtns of counsel and being fully advised in the premises, and having filed a written opinion herein;
It is hereby ordered, that said Writ be, and the same is hereby dismissed, and the petitioner remanded to the custody of the Commissioner of Immigration.
In the District Court of the United States for the Western District of Washington BOB-4-410
In the Matter of the Application of Antonio Bisegna, alias Disegna, for Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Filed in the U.S. District Court, Western Dist. of Washington Northern Division MAR 7 1914 Frank L. Crosby, Clerk By EML Deputy
